    <div class="fullWidth darkStyle" > 
        <div class="container" >        
                      
            <div class="separator_mini"></div> 
            
             <div class="sixteen columns" >
				<div class="mini_description">
                    <p>Of the Old Breed is a World War II interactive narrative that follows the life of a soldier. Users are able to choose what path the soldier goes on and decides the life decisions of their life. Ultimately, the user controls the fate of the soldier, becomes immersed in his story and understands consequences of their actions, along with the emotional impacts on their family.  </p>
                    
                    <p>World War II veterans are quickly fading from our daily lives as time continues to march on. In order to preserve their legacies, memories and experiences this interactive narrative is designed to target a large audience that encompasses military families, veterans, historical fiction fans, students, and “nostalgiaists”. Military families and veterans expect any creative work to be respectful to the military. Fans of historical fiction and students will expect historical accuracy. Nostalgiaists like being immersed in a different time period. All of these demographic groups are highly educated and perceptive. They will expect a story that is not only truthful but illuminates a greater meaning than the characters and events taking place. </p>

<p>Of the Old Breed intends to immerse the viewer in story that places the life, actions, and happiness of soldier in their hands along with reliving famous battles from World War II. Users will expect the characters to be human and tangible. </p>

<p><b>Communication Context </b></p>
<p>This narrative will be a web app that incorporates other visual mediums including photographs, letters, and audio from World War II. Although these other forms of communication are digitized, they will improve the narrative’s tangibility and have kinesthetic effects on the user. </p>

<p><b>Design Implications </b></p>
<p>The user interface needs to follow a visual style in order to reflect the time period. The visual style will incorporate grainy images, muted colors, and handwriting. The HBO series Band of Brothers and The Pacific inspired the art direction Of the Old Breed. The films are vividly rich with textures that resemble the photo graininess and the rough canvas feel of a soldier’s uniforms. As well, they use muted colors to set the bleak, harsh environment of a warfront. The UI will incorporate some skeumorphism, mostly replicating the gritty look of a battlefield. As an interactive narrative, the UI will also be following minimalistic design trends. The images and text are primary focus of attention. </p>
                    
<p><b>Narrative Structure, Performance Objects, Content</b></p>
Narrative Structure
<p>It has a branching structure from a single point where a single starting point may lead to multiple developments and outcomes. This branching structure creates a divergently depth navigation system that is impacted by the user’s choices. Technically there are two navigational flows, the path of the soldier and the screen menus. The soldier’s path traverses on different points, whereas the screen menus will only show four item selections. Whichever item selection is chosen influences the soldier’s course. </p>

<p>Performance Objectives
1.	Present an accurate WWII narrative that immerse the viewer in the story
2.	Show how the consequences of our actions impact family. 
3.	Create an understanding of how soldiers cope with death breathing down their necks. 
The three objectives above outline the overall performance objectives of this piece. Nonetheless, the objectives of each part of the story will be achieved through a series of menus.</p>



